text: Zangberg is a municipality in Mühldorf in Bavaria in Germany. == Geography == Zangberg is in the region Southeast-Upper Bavaria (Südostoberbayern) at the northern part of the valley of the river Isen. There are two local subdistricts: Weilkirchen, Zangberg. The municipality of Zangberg has the following local districts: Atzging, Emerkam, Englhör, Hausmanning, Herrnteisenbach, Kaps, Kröppen, Landenham, Moos, Moosen, Palmberg, Permering, Stegham, Taubenthal, Weiher and Weilkirchen. ==References== Category:Mühldorf (district)
